<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/1002962-been-reading-this-book-couple-o-days-now">Been reading this book couple o days now. Its one of those slow paced easy to read book ( I was hoping for a food for thought kinda book though) anyhoo... is it just me or ... when you read catherine&#39;s dialogue they feel totally fake... like you can&#39;t picture her character... she sounds intense but totally unpredictable ... and than you are like oh probably the author didn&#39;t knew how women think or will react?</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_1002962'><a id="like_count_community_question_1002962" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/1002962?resource_type=CommunityQuestion"><span class="likesCount">25 likes</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F10799.A_Farewell_to_Arms">like</a></span>

